		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">X Window System protocols and architecture</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:102px;"><a href="/wiki/File:X11.svg" class="image" title="The X Window System logo"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/X11.svg/100px-X11.svg.png" width="100" height="100" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:X11.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The X Window System logo</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>In <a href="/wiki/Computing" title="Computing">computing</a>, the <a href="/wiki/X_Window_System" title="X Window System">X Window System</a> (commonly X11 or X) is a <a href="/wiki/Computer_network" title="Computer network">network</a>-transparent <a href="/wiki/Windowing_system" title="Windowing system">windowing system</a> for <a href="/wiki/Raster_graphics" title="Raster graphics">bitmap</a> displays. This article details the protocols and technical structure of X11.</p>
